The following key elements outline the accidental release prevention program for the Edinburg Pump Station No. 1:



$    High level of training of the operators;



$    Preventive maintenance program;



$    Use of state of the art process and safety equipment;



$    Use of accurate and effective operating procedures, written with the participation of the operators;



$    Performance of a hazard review of equipment and procedures;



$    Implementation of an audit and inspection program.



Chemical specific prevention steps include operator use of available Self-Contained-Breathing-Apparatus (SCBA) during connection/disconnection of the chemical supply, awareness of the hazardous and toxic properties of chlorine and the presence of a chemical detector.



No accidental releases of chlorine have occurred at the site in the past five years.



The City of Edinburg=s Fire and Police Departments reviewed the facility=s emergency response program. Both departments are members of the Hidalgo County Local Emergency Planning Committee (LEPC). The program includes an emergency response decision tree and a notification plan. Personnel annually review emergency response drills, drill evaluations, and emergency operation and response procedures.
